Alena said: 'The way it happened, it happened. I'm glad that media were able to cover it and to focus on the problems which face LGBT people.'

Irina said she does intend to change her registration to be a woman. 

'I will change my gender in not less than two years. I am going to change my passport. But what the legal consequences of this will be, I do not know, and have never thought about it.'

The couple married at a registry office in St Petersburg, with both choosing to wear traditional white wedding dresses for the day. 

